reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Fit iPhone 13 Pro Max
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this particular case for my iPhone 13 Pro Max as it had the 3 things I was seeking: Military Grade Shock Proof, camera cover, and kickstand (360 degree ring). A bonus was a “girlie” color. The case fits very snug. After putting the hard shell around the phone, you really need to take time to work the silicone/softer layer around the shell for the perfect fit. I’ve had multi layer cases before and I was aware of this. I used my finger nail to keep space between shell and silicon as I worked around phone to get it in the little groove on the hard shell. Just take your time and it will fit into place. I LOVE the camera cover. I didn’t even know this was something I wanted until I started researching cases for my new phone. When you slide right or left (open or closed) listen for or feel for the little click that locks slider into place. The click is more prevalent as you place over camera side (closed). Maybe in future models they will make it as prevalent on both sides. However, I have shook the phone vigorously in my hand several times with camera cover in open and closed position and it stays in place. It does not slide back and forth. I love the kickstand. It seems sturdy and does what I need it to do. I mostly use the ring to help me hold the phone as I have small hands. I have done the same on previous versions of the phone as well. If you read the specifications it will state there is a place for a credit card. Yes there is a space. However, on this particular case the space is more to “hide” a card. It is not easily accessible. You have to remove the outer hard shell (the layer the kickstand is attached) and place credit card underneath and place shell back on. So if you are looking for a case with credit card wallet, this is not the case for you. This case is a bit bulkier than some but not as bulky as some of the otter box options. I also prefer the price point of this case.
